swapExactTokensForTokens(uint256,uint256.details: Swaps an exact amount of input tokens for as many output tokens as possible, along the route determined by the path.      The first element of path is the input token, the last is the output token, and any intermediate elements represent      intermediate pairs to trade through (if, for example, a direct pair does not exist).

params.amountIn: The amount of input tokens to send.
params.amountOutMin: The minimum amount of output tokens that must be received for the transaction not to revert.
params.deadline: Unix timestamp after which the transaction will revert.
params.path: An array of token addresses. path.length must be >= 2. Pools for each consecutive pair of addresses must exist and have liquidity.

swapExactTokensForTokens(uint256,uint256.return: amounts The input token amount and all subsequent output token amounts.
